race.description: Procon Developments Northam Cup 26 October Hcp
race.comment: TORONADO ROCKET (2) was far too good last start, landing midfield and running over the top of his rivals to score by 1.6L. The rise to 1400m doesn't look an issue and he's shown some adaptability this campaign. May need some luck from the barrier, but Pike sticks and he can bring up back-to-back wins. TASSORT WE WANT (8) was a good winner when sitting on the speed on the Fibre Sand at Bunbury 45 days ago. Up to this trip off a short break is a query, though he looks a very progressive type. Maps for a lovely run and it wouldn't surprise to see him bring up another victory. IDODOMYA (7) got all the way to the Oaks last campaign and showed plenty of ability. Short of her best trip here first-up, but she obviously has some class and Parnham hops on board. Can play a leading role on resumption. ZIPPY ZANY (5) is knocking on the door of another win and is not to be discounted. SHAULA (4) has to be included on recent form.
